<div id="review_1195049376" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1195049376" />
    <a title="Eric" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3170906-eric"><img alt="Eric" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1263902845p2/3170906.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1195049376?book_show_action=true">Feb 08, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eric" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eric" href="/user/show/3170906-eric">Eric</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1195049376" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1835210702526392941">A priest is suspected of pedophile activity.<br/><br/>Whether he did it or not is not really the focus of this play. Rather, the theme is the way in which doubt plays upon the human mind, for good or for ill.<br/><br/>That doesn&apos;t mean you can&apos;t discuss whether or not you feel Father Flynn did it. But the larger grappling with existential doubt is what makes this play more mature and unsettling than the average Afterschool Special.</span>
  <span id="freeText1835210702526392941" style="display:none">A priest is suspected of pedophile activity.<br /><br />Whether he did it or not is not really the focus of this play. Rather, the theme is the way in which doubt plays upon the human mind, for good or for ill.<br /><br />That doesn't mean you can't discuss whether or not you feel Father Flynn did it. But the larger grappling with existential doubt is what makes this play more mature and unsettling than the average Afterschool Special.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1835210702526392941" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


